The paper deals with deep learning and neural networks, which are central topics in machine learning. The focus is on understanding the behavior of deep neural networks as the width of the network increases, which is a topic that falls under the category of deep learning. The experiments are performed on two setups, one of which involves convolutional neural networks, indicating a focus on computer vision applications. The paper also discusses the dynamics of the neural network, which falls under the category of control and optimization. Overall, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
